            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The 1967 Nova received only a minor touchup from the previous year. All Novas got a crosshatch pattern that filled the deck lid trim panel. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It did receive several safety-oriented upgrades like an energy-absorbing steering column and safety steering wheel, along with soft interior parts like armrests and sun visors, recessed instrument panel knobs, and front shoulder belt anchors.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The newly released Camaro stole some of the Nova's sales. Nova's sales dropped by more than a third.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Nova SS got a new black-accented anodized aluminum grille, and SS wheel covers stolen from the Impala SS.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Turbo-Fire 327 was now only available as the 275 hp version.",
